{
  "text": "Cell culture. Lactating female rats of the Sprague-Dawley strain and their pups were purchased from Charles River Labs (Wilmington, MA). Smooth muscle cells were obtained from the thoracic aortas of newborn Sprague-Dawley rats (age: 6 -9 days) as previously described [CITATION_1] . Cells were grown in DMEM-Ham's F-12 medium supplemented with 100 U/ml penicillin, 100 g/ml streptomycin, and 10% FBS in 5% CO 2 at 37\u00b0C. Cultures were maintained in mitogenic quiescence medium lacking FBS for 24 h before being harvested. All experiments in the present study were performed with the use of primary cultures; moreover, each individual experiment represents results from one such cell isolate, generally obtained from one newborn rat litter.",
